HEADWORD: Naturalization
<hw>Nat`u*ral*i*za"tion</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[Cf. F.
<ets>naturalisation</ets>.]</ety> <def>The act or process of
naturalizing, esp. of investing an alien with the rights and privileges
of a native or citizen; also, the state of being naturalized.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

